      "text": "For test cases S3\nURL(6.5)",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "Fra4AfQvODrPUC48V5Fdq",
      "originalText": "For test cases S3 URL(6.5)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "l5c1D89S7gOURRhz7JBYx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 492.2010559371538,
      "y": -10815.073686045409,
      "width": 2393.603271484375,
      "height": 1035,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#96f2d7",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b97",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1682964861,
      "version": 1965,
      "versionNonce": 614019933,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768568994499,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "To perform 5th operation we are waiting for 4th sync operation, with this synchronous mechanism there are a couple of problem\n1. this is relatively slightly slower process -> two operation involver 1 -> making an entry to the submission DB\n                                                                                    2 -> making an entry to the submission queue after getting res\n                                                                                           from the submission DB.\nSo even if workers running in Evaluator service are completely free they still have to wait for the submission DB to give the corres-\nponding response\n\n2. to solve this problem we might parallise the call we will make entry to the submission DB and submission queue parallely, this is \nalternative mecahnism that we can think about but we go to parallel operation there is one more thing that our synchronous operation\nhas to handle, what if we made an entry to the submission DB but while making an entry in the submission queue we were never able to \nmake an entry in the submission queue. why -> may be our application server crashed or for a time being there is network latency or\nnetwork issue, time out happend or queue went down anything can go wrong or vice versa we were able to make an entry to the\nsubmission queue but DB crashed due to any reason like DB is overloaded with no of requests\n\n\nSO while designing any system we need to keep one thing in mind always that if there is a possibility to reduce the no of entries all \ntogether then we should try to somehow do that\n\n\nThen what is alternative ->\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "To perform 5th operation we are waiting for 4th sync operation, with this synchronous mechanism there are a couple of problem\n1. this is relatively slightly slower process -> two operation involver 1 -> making an entry to the submission DB\n                                                                                    2 -> making an entry to the submission queue after getting res\n                                                                                           from the submission DB.\nSo even if workers running in Evaluator service are completely free they still have to wait for the submission DB to give the corres-\nponding response\n\n2. to solve this problem we might parallise the call we will make entry to the submission DB and submission queue parallely, this is \nalternative mecahnism that we can think about but we go to parallel operation there is one more thing that our synchronous operation\nhas to handle, what if we made an entry to the submission DB but while making an entry in the submission queue we were never able to \nmake an entry in the submission queue. why -> may be our application server crashed or for a time being there is network latency or\nnetwork issue, time out happend or queue went down anything can go wrong or vice versa we were able to make an entry to the\nsubmission queue but DB crashed due to any reason like DB is overloaded with no of requests\n\n\nSO while designing any system we need to keep one thing in mind always that if there is a possibility to reduce the no of entries all \ntogether then we should try to somehow do that\n\n\nThen what is alternative ->\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
