    {
      "id": "IaQNNGB6zgmmq1Iq0oeMM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1729.7994414348,
      "y": -7224.706584385818,
      "width": 1101.7796630859375,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#fff0f6",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 419272079,
      "version": 684,
      "versionNonce": 1307528047,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768740424855,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Very similar to message queueing system with one big diff\nthat multiple consumers can read same message.\nMessage Queue system like RabbitMQ etc generally supports\nexactly one or atmost one delivery, where as message streams\nsupports atleast 1 delivery that means produce the data once\nand it can be read more than once or by more that 1 consumer.\nAnd if somehow we have this system available which is scalable\nenough and supports this feature then our problem is solved\nand this is sovled by message streams\nExample -> Apache Kafka, AWS Kinesis",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Very similar to message queueing system with one big diff\nthat multiple consumers can read same message.\nMessage Queue system like RabbitMQ etc generally supports\nexactly one or atmost one delivery, where as message streams\nsupports atleast 1 delivery that means produce the data once\nand it can be read more than once or by more that 1 consumer.\nAnd if somehow we have this system available which is scalable\nenough and supports this feature then our problem is solved\nand this is sovled by message streams\nExample -> Apache Kafka, AWS Kinesis",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
