    },
    {
      "id": "RO_7gK-Jdn4i0ynmYGqUW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1647.2916289348,
      "y": -6466.542521885818,
      "width": 1271.735595703125,
      "height": 360,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#fff0f6",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9p",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 193845391,
      "version": 378,
      "versionNonce": 1026977999,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768740600949,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It is a message streaming system, Its open source and FYI this is\nmade in LinkedIN.\n\nGood Part about message streams is in most of the case where\nmessage queue works fine, Message stream is also fit very well.\n\nApart from this Kafka is very highly scalable , highly durable and delivers\nextremely high performance.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It is a message streaming system, Its open source and FYI this is\nmade in LinkedIN.\n\nGood Part about message streams is in most of the case where\nmessage queue works fine, Message stream is also fit very well.\n\nApart from this Kafka is very highly scalable , highly durable and delivers\nextremely high performance.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "y-xCa4h4WjrvthFZO_31J",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 645.4088164348,
      "y": -6124.714396885818,
      "width": 2318.399169921875,
      "height": 765,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#fff0f6",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1485520705,
      "version": 1821,
      "versionNonce": 85273967,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "DGyLEULMnpVdXzJnkOeC6",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1768741669674,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "With the help of kafka we dont need submission queue any more and our Evaluator service can become\na direct consumer of kafka, theretically if we make an entry to the kafka it will be in kafa forever,\n hence our infra will be can\n\nIf Submission service has produce the data in kafka, we can successfully record the fact that your submission\nhas been received. we dont need to wait for a db entry to be made before we respond back to the client. because of \nthe fact the kafka is extremely durable solution.\n\nThen why we even need to make an entry to DB?\nIf User want to see their submissions or older submissions then those calls will be directly responded back from the Database.\nbecause we can keep things in kafka forever but generally we don't. and we will talk about how exactly consumers read from\nkafka so we will realize the use case that client has to see their older submissions has to be resolved from the DB only. we will\nget this answer later,\nbut the thing is submission server doesn't need to wait for an entry to be made in DB. If we have successfully made and entry \ninside kafka we can be rest assured. that our entry will be eventually made in the DB by the corresponding consumer that consumer\ncan be separate service or same submission service also. and we can immediately respond back to the client we have recorded your\nsubmission.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "With the help of kafka we dont need submission queue any more and our Evaluator service can become\na direct consumer of kafka, theretically if we make an entry to the kafka it will be in kafa forever,\n hence our infra will be can\n\nIf Submission service has produce the data in kafka, we can successfully record the fact that your submission\nhas been received. we dont need to wait for a db entry to be made before we respond back to the client. because of \nthe fact the kafka is extremely durable solution.\n\nThen why we even need to make an entry to DB?\nIf User want to see their submissions or older submissions then those calls will be directly responded back from the Database.\nbecause we can keep things in kafka forever but generally we don't. and we will talk about how exactly consumers read from\nkafka so we will realize the use case that client has to see their older submissions has to be resolved from the DB only. we will\nget this answer later,\nbut the thing is submission server doesn't need to wait for an entry to be made in DB. If we have successfully made and entry \ninside kafka we can be rest assured. that our entry will be eventually made in the DB by the corresponding consumer that consumer\ncan be separate service or same submission service also. and we can immediately respond back to the client we have recorded your\nsubmission.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "bkZso9gS4dNPpJ4Co14Lp",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 910.6960732626128,
      "y": -5211.390216469259,
      "width": 224.04966112687188,
      "height": 117.96059068287356,
      "angle": 0.007660493732935869,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bAH",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 2052826703,
      "version": 663,
      "versionNonce": 861586305,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
