    {
      "id": "reKErW8dvbtZvI2342mL7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 707.8489206014656,
      "y": -4319.667521885829,
      "width": 2379.131591796875,
      "height": 810,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bAc",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1881350529,
      "version": 1233,
      "versionNonce": 306467043,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768827520837,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How exactly kafka handles things all together?\nthere are some of the terms that we need to first clear in our head \n\n- Producer\n- Consumer\n- Topic\n- Partition\n\nthese are 4 most imp term that we have to understand if we dont understand them we are not able to answer any corresponding\nquestion around kafka, because kafka is one of those topics in our infra interview or system interview where we have to not just \nsay that I will introduce kafka in place of submission queue and things will be automatically done. People will expect from us what\nwe will do with kafka, how we will setup things with kafka, how exactly things will be managed all together. this is someting that we\nhave to answer.\n\nIts not just that we need to know there is a very scalable system , very scalable message framing system like kafka which if we will\nintroduce, will solve the scalability problem for us, we also need to know how we will set it up or what solution we are going to prepare.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How exactly kafka handles things all together?\nthere are some of the terms that we need to first clear in our head \n\n- Producer\n- Consumer\n- Topic\n- Partition\n\nthese are 4 most imp term that we have to understand if we dont understand them we are not able to answer any corresponding\nquestion around kafka, because kafka is one of those topics in our infra interview or system interview where we have to not just \nsay that I will introduce kafka in place of submission queue and things will be automatically done. People will expect from us what\nwe will do with kafka, how we will setup things with kafka, how exactly things will be managed all together. this is someting that we\nhave to answer.\n\nIts not just that we need to know there is a very scalable system , very scalable message framing system like kafka which if we will\nintroduce, will solve the scalability problem for us, we also need to know how we will set it up or what solution we are going to prepare.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
