      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768827812118,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Consumer-> whatever the data will be read from queue\nwill be read by Consumer. Consumere is responsible for\nreading these events or data from the queue.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Consumer-> whatever the data will be read from queue\nwill be read by Consumer. Consumere is responsible for\nreading these events or data from the queue.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "_mQqesBeAGwEzbCxA643K",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 810.361412463445,
      "y": -2558.5399177191575,
      "width": 2186.99951171875,
      "height": 315,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "#fff5f5",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bAu",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 316552611,
      "version": 657,
      "versionNonce": 34850509,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768828178349,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Lets take an example where kafka can outshine alot of other solution as well, For example there is an application like UBER\none of the fundamental operation in Uber is\n- Updating Driver Location -> If we can't record latest driver locations then most of the thing in UBER like system are no\nsence, LIke our user will not able to know where driver is going to come, we will not able to know how much time will driver is\ngoing to take in order to reach the location to pick up the User.\n\nHow we thing we will update the driver location -> ",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Lets take an example where kafka can outshine alot of other solution as well, For example there is an application like UBER\none of the fundamental operation in Uber is\n- Updating Driver Location -> If we can't record latest driver locations then most of the thing in UBER like system are no\nsence, LIke our user will not able to know where driver is going to come, we will not able to know how much time will driver is\ngoing to take in order to reach the location to pick up the User.\n\nHow we thing we will update the driver location -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
