      "text": "Lets say Driver app somehow fetched the Geo locations\nthen server is hit by client, how we will store these location, \ndo we directly store into DB -> I dont think this is good way why?\n\nthink about scale at Uber -> More than 4 to 5 Million Driver in Uber in a specific region \nwe can consider at Peak office hours, all of the drivers must be moving then we need to actually populate or we need to \nactually record their latest live location very frequently like generally it should be in every 10 sec or 5 sec we would like\nto know our driver updated location so every single driver app will going to bombard our server with humoungous no of \nrequest and lets say we are able to scale our server with all of those request no problem. but do we want to put all of\nthose bombarded requests to our DB probably not. Our DB is relatively more crucial for us \n1 more issue here -> we dont juse need our drivers latest location, we probably need our driver complete location trace why?\nto track like sometime user dispute that driver took a separate route. for that we need to know the route that what exact\nroute the driver actually took for that we need the location data of the driver through out the trip so it is not about updating\nour database with the latest location its also about storing or recording all the corresponding events all the corresponding\nlatitude and logitude changes. \n\nWe can think we will put a queue, server will produce on queue and there will be a consumer that will solwly put the data into DB.\nbut that will also not solve our problem fully. because our normal queue can't keep our data forever. The moment data is read by\nconsumer, data is gone from the Queue. Plus we also need to make sure this queue is scaled properly, ",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Lets say Driver app somehow fetched the Geo locations\nthen server is hit by client, how we will store these location, \ndo we directly store into DB -> I dont think this is good way why?\n\nthink about scale at Uber -> More than 4 to 5 Million Driver in Uber in a specific region \nwe can consider at Peak office hours, all of the drivers must be moving then we need to actually populate or we need to \nactually record their latest live location very frequently like generally it should be in every 10 sec or 5 sec we would like\nto know our driver updated location so every single driver app will going to bombard our server with humoungous no of \nrequest and lets say we are able to scale our server with all of those request no problem. but do we want to put all of\nthose bombarded requests to our DB probably not. Our DB is relatively more crucial for us \n1 more issue here -> we dont juse need our drivers latest location, we probably need our driver complete location trace why?\nto track like sometime user dispute that driver took a separate route. for that we need to know the route that what exact\nroute the driver actually took for that we need the location data of the driver through out the trip so it is not about updating\nour database with the latest location its also about storing or recording all the corresponding events all the corresponding\nlatitude and logitude changes. \n\nWe can think we will put a queue, server will produce on queue and there will be a consumer that will solwly put the data into DB.\nbut that will also not solve our problem fully. because our normal queue can't keep our data forever. The moment data is read by\nconsumer, data is gone from the Queue. Plus we also need to make sure this queue is scaled properly, ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
